# PRD: Advanced Sudoku Web App — MVP

## 1. Product summary

The MVP is a clean, mobile-first Sudoku web app for playing curated puzzles with strong usability, local save/resume, mistake detection, corner notes, undo/redo, highlighting, and light/dark mode.

The app will be a frontend-only React app hosted as a static site. Puzzle sets will be provided manually as bundled JSON data. Game state and settings will be stored locally in the browser using IndexedDB.

The MVP will not include puzzle generation, cloud sync, user accounts, leaderboards, advanced hinting, PWA/offline support, testing infrastructure, or a puzzle validation script.

---

## 2. MVP goals

| Goal | Description |
|---|---|
| Provide a clean Sudoku playing experience | The app should feel simple, fast, and uncluttered. |
| Support curated puzzle sets | Initial puzzles will be provided manually by difficulty. |
| Make mobile play comfortable | Controls should work well on phones in portrait and landscape. |
| Preserve game state locally | Users should be able to close the browser and resume later. |
| Support common Sudoku workflows | Cell-first and number-first play should both be supported. |
| Reduce input friction | Notes, clearing cells, undo/redo, and number entry should be easy. |

## 3. Success criteria

| Metric | Target |
|---|---|
| User can start a puzzle in under 3 taps | Required |
| User can resume an unfinished puzzle after closing browser | Required |
| User can enter answers and notes without confusion | Required |
| User can complete a puzzle and see a win screen | Required |
| Puzzle state survives browser refresh | Required |
| App works well on mobile browsers | Required |

---

## 4. Non-goals for MVP

| Excluded Feature | Reason |
|---|---|
| Puzzle generator | User will provide initial puzzle sets. |
| Cloud sync | IndexedDB/local storage is enough for MVP. |
| User accounts | Not needed for personal-use MVP. |
| Leaderboards | Not relevant yet. |
| Daily puzzle | Can be added later. |
| Advanced hint engine | Too large for MVP. |
| Technique trainer | Better as a later advanced feature. |
| PWA/offline support | Not needed for MVP. |
| Formal testing setup | Not needed for MVP. |
| Puzzle validation script | Not needed for MVP. |
| Full desktop optimization | Mobile is the priority. |
| Puzzle sharing | Useful later, not required now. |
| Full statistics dashboard | Completion screen and basic local history are enough initially. |

---

## 5. Tech stack

| Layer | MVP Choice | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Frontend framework | React | Main app framework |
| Language | TypeScript | Strong typing for board state, moves, settings, and puzzle metadata |
| Build tool | Vite | Fast React development and simple static build output |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS | Clean responsive styling and easy light/dark mode |
| Local database | IndexedDB | Stores active game, settings, and completed games |
| IndexedDB wrapper | Dexie.js | Cleaner API than raw IndexedDB |
| Hosting | GitHub Pages | Static hosting |
| Puzzle source | Bundled JSON files | User-provided initial puzzle sets |
| Backend | None | Not needed for MVP |
| Auth | None | Not needed for MVP |
| PWA/offline | None | Explicitly excluded |
| Testing | None | Explicitly excluded |
| Validation script | None | Explicitly excluded |

Recommended stack:

```txt id="zwbggy"
React
TypeScript
Vite
Tailwind CSS
Dexie.js
IndexedDB
Bundled JSON puzzle files
GitHub Pages
No backend
No auth
No PWA
No testing setup
No validation script
```

---

## 6. Architecture

The app should still be organized so future features can be added without gutting the board logic.

Recommended services/modules:

| Module | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| `PuzzleService` | Loads bundled puzzle JSON by difficulty |
| `GameStateService` | Creates, updates, saves, and restores active games |
| `SettingsService` | Handles theme and user settings |
| `StorageService` | Wraps Dexie/IndexedDB access |
| `TimerService` | Tracks elapsed time and pause/resume behavior |
| `MoveHistoryService` | Handles undo/redo stacks |
| `BoardUtils` | Contains Sudoku board/index helper functions |
| `HighlightUtils` | Computes selected cell, row, column, box, and same-digit highlights |

Suggested folder structure:

```txt id="cvt0qe"
src/
  components/
    Board/
    Cell/
    NumberPad/
    Timer/
    Menu/
    CompletionScreen/
  data/
    puzzles.easy.json
    puzzles.medium.json
    puzzles.hard.json
    puzzles.expert.json
  hooks/
    useGameState.ts
    useTimer.ts
    useSettings.ts
  services/
    puzzleService.ts
    storageService.ts
    gameStateService.ts
    moveHistoryService.ts
  types/
    puzzle.ts
    gameState.ts
    move.ts
    settings.ts
  utils/
    boardUtils.ts
    highlightUtils.ts
```

---

## 7. Target platform

| Platform | MVP Support |
|---|---|
| Android mobile browser | Primary |
| Desktop browser | Basic support |
| Tablet browser | Supported through responsive layout |
| PWA installability | Not included |
| Offline support | Not included |

The app should be designed mobile-first, but desktop should not be broken.

---

## 8. Core user flows

## 8.1 Start a new puzzle

1. User opens app.
2. User selects difficulty: Easy, Medium, Hard, or Expert.
3. App selects a puzzle from that difficulty.
4. App loads puzzle grid.
5. Timer starts automatically unless app is opened in paused state.

| Requirement | Priority |
|---|---|
| Difficulty selector must be accessible from main menu/start screen | Must |
| App must load puzzles from bundled JSON files | Must |
| App should avoid serving the same puzzle repeatedly | Should |
| If an active puzzle exists, app should ask whether to resume or start new | Should |

---

## 8.2 Resume current puzzle

1. User reopens the app.
2. App checks IndexedDB for active puzzle.
3. App restores board state, notes, timer, mistake count, selected settings, and undo history.
4. User continues playing.

| Requirement | Priority |
|---|---|
| Current board state must persist | Must |
| Notes must persist | Must |
| Timer state must persist | Must |
| Mistake count must persist | Must |
| Undo/redo history should persist | Should |
| Paused state should persist | Should |

---

## 8.3 Cell-first workflow

1. User taps a cell.
2. User taps a number.
3. App enters answer or note depending on current input mode.

| Requirement | Priority |
|---|---|
| Selected cell must be visually obvious | Must |
| Number pad must input into selected cell | Must |
| Locked givens cannot be edited | Must |
| Input mode must be obvious | Must |

---

## 8.4 Number-first workflow

1. User selects a number.
2. User taps cells where that number should be entered.
3. App places that number into tapped cells, respecting answer/note mode.

| Requirement | Priority |
|---|---|
| Selected number must be visually obvious | Must |
| Tapping a cell after number selection must apply selected number | Must |
| User must be able to switch between cell-first and number-first naturally | Should |
| App should not require a dedicated setting just to use either workflow | Should |

---

## 8.5 Enter notes

MVP note style: **corner notes only**.

1. User toggles note mode.
2. User selects a cell.
3. User taps one or more numbers.
4. App toggles those candidate marks in the selected cell.

| Requirement | Priority |
|---|---|
| Note mode must be visually distinct from answer mode | Must |
| Candidate numbers must be readable on mobile | Must |
| Tapping an existing candidate should remove it | Must |
| Entering a final answer should clear notes in that cell | Must |
| Auto-remove notes from peers should be optional | Must |

---

## 8.6 Mistake detection

MVP behavior:

```txt id="3nmc3t"
Wrong answer flashes red and is rejected.
```

| Requirement | Priority |
|---|---|
| App must compare entered value against solution string | Must |
| Wrong entry must produce immediate visual feedback | Must |
| Wrong entry should increase mistake count | Should |
| Wrong entry should not be added to board | Should |
| Mistake animation should be brief and non-annoying | Should |

---

## 8.7 Pause/resume timer

1. User taps timer.
2. App pauses timer.
3. App hides board.
4. User taps resume.
5. App reveals board and continues timer.

| Requirement | Priority |
|---|---|
| Timer must pause when user taps it | Must |
| Board must be hidden while paused | Must |
| Timer must resume accurately | Must |
| Paused state should survive browser refresh | Should |

---

## 8.8 Undo/redo

Undo/redo must support:

| Action Type | Undo/Redo Support |
|---|---|
| Answer entry | Required |
| Answer clear | Required |
| Note add/remove | Required |
| Auto-removed notes | Required if auto-remove is enabled |
| Mistake attempt | Optional, because incorrect entries are rejected |

| Requirement | Priority |
|---|---|
| User can undo most recent valid board-changing action | Must |
| User can redo after undo | Must |
| New action after undo clears redo stack | Must |
| Undo/redo must preserve notes accurately | Must |

---

## 8.9 Complete puzzle

1. User fills final correct cell.
2. App detects completion.
3. App stops timer.
4. App shows win screen.

| Field | MVP |
|---|---|
| Difficulty | Required |
| Final time | Required |
| Mistake count | Optional but recommended |
| New puzzle button | Required |
| Replay/reset button | Optional |
| Back to menu button | Required |

---

## 9. Functional requirements

## 9.1 Interface

| Feature | Requirement | Priority |
|---|---|---|
| Nice clean interface | App must have a clean, uncluttered Sudoku board and controls | Must |
| Menu | App must include a menu for settings and new puzzle flow | Must |
| Timer | Timer must be visible but not visually dominant | Must |
| Light mode | App defaults to light mode | Must |
| Dark mode | User can toggle dark mode | Must |
| Theme persistence | Theme preference is saved locally | Must |

---

## 9.2 Puzzle difficulty

Supported difficulties:

```txt id="3fnqpd"
Easy
Medium
Hard
Expert
```

| Requirement | Priority |
|---|---|
| Each puzzle must have a difficulty value | Must |
| Difficulty selector must use the four MVP difficulty values | Must |
| App must load puzzles from provided initial sets | Must |
| App must gracefully handle an empty difficulty set | Must |

---

## 9.3 Puzzle metadata

Each puzzle should include:

```ts id="9n5nba"
type Difficulty = "Easy" | "Medium" | "Hard" | "Expert";

type Puzzle = {
  id: string;
  difficulty: Difficulty;
  source: string;
  puzzle: string;
  solution: string;
  createdDate: string;
};
```

Example:

```json id="w51cl4"
{
  "id": "hard-0001",
  "difficulty": "Hard",
  "source": "initial-set",
  "puzzle": "5,3,null,null,7,null,null,null,null,6,null,null,1,9,5,null,null,null,null,9,8,null,null,null,null,6,null,8,null,null,null,6,null,null,null,3,4,null,null,8,null,3,null,null,1,7,null,null,null,2,null,null,null,6,null,6,null,null,null,2,8,null,null,null,4,1,9,null,null,null,8,null,null,null,7,9",
  "solution": "5,3,4,6,7,8,9,1,2,6,7,2,1,9,5,3,4,8,1,9,8,3,4,2,5,6,7,8,5,9,7,6,1,4,2,3,4,2,6,8,5,3,7,9,1,7,1,3,9,2,4,8,5,6,9,6,1,5,3,7,2,8,4,2,8,7,4,1,9,6,3,5,3,4,5,2,8,6,1,7,9",
  "createdDate": "2026-05-13"
}
```

| Requirement | Priority |
|---|---|
| Puzzle ID must be unique | Must |
| Puzzle string must be 81 characters | Must |
| Solution string must be 81 characters | Must |
| Difficulty must be stored | Must |
| Source must be stored | Should |
| Created date must be stored | Should |

---

## 9.4 Board rules

| Rule | Requirement |
|---|---|
| Givens are locked | User cannot change original puzzle clues |
| User entries are editable | User can clear or replace own entries |
| Notes only allowed in empty cells | Filled cells should not display notes |
| Completion requires correct solution | Board must match solution string |
| Mistake detection uses solution | Incorrect entries compare against known solution |

---

## 9.5 Highlighting

| Highlight Type | Requirement |
|---|---|
| Selected cell | Highlight selected cell clearly |
| Same row | Highlight row of selected cell |
| Same column | Highlight column of selected cell |
| Same 3x3 box | Highlight box of selected cell |
| Same digit | Highlight matching digits |
| Error/mistake | Flash incorrect entry cell |

Highlighting should be helpful but not visually overwhelming.

---

## 9.6 Auto-remove notes

When enabled, entering a correct answer removes that number from notes in all peer cells:

```txt id="qk4vk5"
same row
same column
same 3x3 box
```

| Requirement | Priority |
|---|---|
| User can toggle auto-remove notes | Must |
| Setting persists locally | Should |
| Auto-removals must be undoable | Must |
| Auto-remove should only happen after valid answer entry | Must |

---

## 9.7 Local save/resume

The app will use IndexedDB through Dexie.js.

| Data | Required |
|---|---|
| Current puzzle ID | Yes |
| Board state | Yes |
| Notes | Yes |
| Timer elapsed seconds | Yes |
| Mistake count | Yes |
| Undo stack | Yes |
| Redo stack | Recommended |
| Theme setting | Yes |
| Auto-remove notes setting | Recommended |
| Current input mode | Recommended |
| Completed puzzle history | Recommended |

---

## 10. Data model

## 10.1 Cell state

```ts id="jkcw4a"
type CellState = {
  index: number;
  given: boolean;
  value: number | null;
  notes: number[];
};
```

## 10.2 Game state

```ts id="6v28q6"
type GameState = {
  puzzleId: string;
  grid: CellState[];
  elapsedSeconds: number;
  mistakeCount: number;
  isPaused: boolean;
  isComplete: boolean;
  selectedCellIndex: number | null;
  selectedNumber: number | null;
  inputMode: "answer" | "note";
  workflowMode: "cell-first" | "number-first" | "auto";
  undoStack: Move[];
  redoStack: Move[];
  startedAt: string;
  updatedAt: string;
};
```

## 10.3 Move history

```ts id="q1786v"
type Move = {
  id: string;
  timestamp: string;
  type: "set-value" | "clear-value" | "toggle-note" | "auto-remove-notes" | "fill-candidates";
  cellIndex: number;
  previousState: CellState;
  nextState: CellState;
  affectedCells?: {
    cellIndex: number;
    previousState: CellState;
    nextState: CellState;
  }[];
};
```

## 10.4 Settings

```ts id="f4v2gl"
type Settings = {
  theme: "light" | "dark";
  inputMode: "answer" | "note";
};
```

## 10.5 Completed game

```ts id="t7mhd2"
type CompletedGame = {
  id: string;
  puzzleId: string;
  difficulty: Difficulty;
  elapsedSeconds: number;
  mistakeCount: number;
  completedAt: string;
};
```

## 10.6 Seen puzzle

```ts id="seen-puzzle"
type SeenPuzzle = {
  id: string;
  puzzleId: string;
  difficulty: Difficulty;
  seenAt: string;
};
```

---

## 11. IndexedDB stores

| Store | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `activeGame` | Current in-progress puzzle |
| `completedGames` | Finished puzzle records |
| `seenPuzzles` | Puzzles already started or restored |
| `settings` | Theme and user preferences |

The bundled puzzle data does not need to be imported into IndexedDB for MVP. It can remain static JSON in the app bundle.

Recommended:

```txt id="g9o2tu"
Bundled JSON = puzzle source of truth
IndexedDB = user state and progress
```

---

