## 13. Mobile control behavior

## 13.1 Number pad

The number pad should include:

```txt id="xcuvdk"
1 2 3
4 5 6
7 8 9
```

Additional controls:

```txt id="xqpnde"
Note
Erase
Undo
Redo
```

| Requirement | Priority |
|---|---|
| Buttons must be large enough for touch input | Must |
| Current input mode must be obvious | Must |
| Selected number must be obvious | Must |
| Erase must be easy to find | Must |
| Undo/redo must not be too easy to tap accidentally | Should |

## 13.2 Tap/hold behavior

| Gesture | Behavior |
|---|---|
| Tap cell | Select cell |
| Tap number | Enter selected number or note |
| Long-press cell | Optional shortcut to note mode |
| Long-press number | Optional alternate note entry |

Core play must not depend on long-press. Long-press can be a shortcut only.

---

## 14. Portrait and landscape mode

## 14.1 Portrait

Portrait is the primary layout.

Expected order:

```txt id="b6zhes"
Header / timer
Sudoku grid
Input mode controls
Number pad
Footer/menu controls
```

## 14.2 Landscape

Landscape should remain usable.

Possible layout:

```txt id="xakgvo"
Sudoku grid on left
Number pad and controls on right
```

| Requirement | Priority |
|---|---|
| App must not break in landscape mode | Must |
| Board must remain fully visible | Must |
| Number pad must remain usable | Must |
| No horizontal scrolling | Should |

---

## 15. Runtime data handling

Because the MVP will not include a validation script, the app should assume bundled puzzle data is trusted.

However, the app should still handle obvious runtime failures gracefully.

| Case | Behavior |
|---|---|
| Missing puzzle set | Show friendly error |
| Empty difficulty set | Show friendly error |
| Invalid puzzle ID | Return to menu |
| Corrupted active game | Offer to reset current puzzle |
| IndexedDB unavailable | Show warning and continue without persistence if possible |
| Completed puzzle reopened | Show completed state or allow replay |

Do not build a full puzzle validator for MVP.

---

## 16. Settings

MVP settings:

| Setting | Default | Persisted |
|---|---:|---:|
| Theme | Light | Yes |
| Auto-remove notes | On | Yes |
| Input mode | Answer | Session or persisted |
| Mistake detection | On | No setting needed for MVP |

Recommended defaults:

```txt id="c34ipk"
Theme: Light
Auto-remove notes: On
Input mode: Answer
Mistake detection: On
```

---

## 17. Acceptance criteria

## 17.1 New puzzle

- User can select Easy, Medium, Hard, or Expert.
- App loads a puzzle from selected difficulty.
- Board displays givens correctly.
- Givens cannot be edited.
- Timer starts.

## 17.2 Answer entry

- User can select a cell.
- User can enter a number.
- Correct number appears in the cell.
- Incorrect number flashes red.
- Incorrect number is not entered.
- Mistake count increments.

## 17.3 Notes

- User can toggle note mode.
- User can add corner notes to empty cells.
- User can remove existing notes.
- Notes persist after refresh.
- Notes can be undone/redone.

## 17.4 Undo/redo

- User can undo answer entry.
- User can undo cell clearing.
- User can undo note changes.
- User can redo undone changes.
- Redo stack clears after a new move.

## 17.5 Highlighting

- Selected cell is highlighted.
- Same row, column, and box are highlighted.
- Same digit is highlighted.
- Highlighting updates after selection changes.

## 17.6 Pause/resume

- User can tap timer to pause.
- Timer stops.
- Board is hidden.
- User can resume.
- Timer continues from previous value.

## 17.7 Completion

- App detects solved puzzle.
- Timer stops.
- Completion screen appears.
- Completion screen shows time and difficulty.
- User can start a new puzzle.

## 17.8 Persistence

- App saves active puzzle.
- App saves board state.
- App saves notes.
- App saves timer.
- App saves theme.
- Refreshing page restores state.

---

## 18. Implementation phases

## Phase 1 — React app shell and board

- Create React + TypeScript + Vite project.
- Add Tailwind CSS.
- Build responsive Sudoku grid.
- Load local puzzle JSON.
- Show givens.
- Select cells.
- Enter answers.
- Lock givens.

## Phase 2 — Core gameplay

- Timer.
- Pause/resume.
- Hide board while paused.
- Mistake detection.
- Highlighting.
- Completion detection.
- Win screen.

## Phase 3 — Notes and controls

- Note mode.
- Corner notes.
- Number pad.
- Erase.
- Cell-first workflow.
- Number-first workflow.
- Input mode indicator.

## Phase 4 — Local persistence

- Add Dexie.js.
- Create IndexedDB stores.
- Save active game.
- Restore active game.
- Save settings.
- Store completed games.

## Phase 5 — Polish

- Undo/redo.
- Auto-remove notes.
- Portrait layout tuning.
- Landscape layout tuning.
- Dark mode.
- Runtime error handling.
- GitHub Pages deployment.

---

## 19. Open product decisions

| Decision | Recommended MVP Choice |
|---|---|
| Wrong answer behavior | Reject and flash red |
| Auto-remove notes default | On |
| Note input behavior | Tap controls first; long-press optional later |
| Number-first mode | Automatic |
| Puzzle selection | Random uncompleted puzzle |
| Puzzle storage | Bundled JSON |
| Active game storage | IndexedDB |
| Desktop support | Basic only |
| PWA/offline | Excluded |
| Testing | Excluded |
| Validation script | Excluded |

---

# MVP summary

```txt id="kluklp"
A React + TypeScript mobile-first Sudoku web app with curated puzzles, local IndexedDB save/resume, corner notes, mistake detection, highlighting, undo/redo, pause/resume timer, light/dark mode, and a simple completion screen.
```

The most important implementation principle:

```txt id="oyrmey"
Build a Sudoku board that feels excellent to use before adding advanced solving, hints, puzzle generation, accounts, or stats.
```
